'''Al Ayal Kibrit''' ''(The Kids Have Grown Up, العيَال كبرت)'' is a famous [[Egypt]]ian play starring [[Saeed Saleh]], [[Ahmad Zaki (actor)|Ahmad Zaki]], Yunis Shalabi, and Nadia Shoukry as the [[children]]. Hassan Mustafa plays the role of the [[father]] with [[Karima Mokhtar]] playing the role of the mother. The play tells the story of the children trying to stop their father from leaving his family for another woman after one of them accidentally finds a love letter from an unknown woman to their father.

==Note==
*This is the second play Sa'ed Saleh, [[Ahmad Zaki (actor)|Ahmad Zaki]], Yunis Shalabi, and Hassan Mustafa starred in together since the play [[Madrast Al-Mushaghebeen]].

