The '''Guinea-Bissau riot of 2007''' was a protest by [[Guinea-Bissau|Bissauan]] civilians in the [[Bairro Militar]] District, a [[suburb]] of the capital, [[Bissau]]. It was staged against the murder of former [[Military of Guinea-Bissau|Navy]] chief, [[Mohamed Lamine Sanha]]. The police opened fire on the protesters, killing one man.<ref>[http://english.aljazeera.net/NR/exeres/A479C2D6-577D-4E54-8645-C8C8F6818ED4.htm Protesters shot in Guinea-Bissau] Al-Jazeera English, 7 January 2007</ref>

