{{Infobox network | name = IRIB World Service | logo = | country = [[Iran]] | network_type = [[Radio network]] | available = International | owner = [[Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting]] | key_people = | launch_date = 1956 | past_names = | website = {{URL|http://www.ws.irib.ir/}} |}}
'''IRIB World Service''', ''irib'' is the official [[international broadcasting]] radio network of [[Iran]].
The radio network started to work in 1956 with the aim of familiarizing different world nations with Iran’s history and culture as well as its different regions and historical sites. Following the [[Iranian Revolution]], elaborating on the revolution’s stances and the ideals of the Islamic Republic system were put high on the radio’s agenda.<ref name="irib1">[http://english.irib.ir/home/about-us About us: IRIB English Radio]. Retrieved on 15 August 2014.</ref>
The radio’s schedule includes news and talk programmes, political and religious commentaries, different series and features on special occasions.
==Languages== The IRIB World Service currently broadcasts in 32 languages: {|width=45% |-valign=top |width=15%|
* [[Albanian language|Albanian]] * [[Modern Standard Arabic|Arabic]] * Aran * [[Armenian language|Armenian]] * [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]] * [[Bengali language|Bengali]] |width=15%| * [[Bosnian language|Bosnian]] * [[Chinese language|Chinese]] * [[Dari (Eastern Persian)|Dari]] * English * [[French language|French]] * [[Georgian language|Georgian]] |width=15%| * [[German language|German]] * [[Hausa language|Hausa]] * [[Modern Hebrew|Hebrew]] * [[Hindi language|Hindi]] * [[Indonesian language|Indonesian]] * [[Italian language|Italian]] |width=15%| * [[Japanese language|Japanese]] * [[Kazakh language|Kazakh]] * [[Kurdish language|Kurdish]] * [[Pushto language|Pashto]] * [[Persian language|Persian]] * [[Russian language|Russian]] |width=15%| * [[Spanish language|Spanish]] * [[Swahili language|Swahili]] * [[Tajik language|Tajik]] * [[Talysh language|Talysh]] * [[Turkish language|Turkish]] * [[Turkmen language|Turkmen]] |width=15%| * [[Urdu language|Urdu]] * [[Uzbek language|Uzbek]] |}
=== English Radio === '''English Radio''' is the [[English language]] output of the IRIB World Service, aimed to the listeners in the [[English-speaking world]].<ref name="irib1" /> '''Voice of Justice''' is a 60-minute-long programming block, aimed to listeners in the [[United States]].<ref>[http://www.clandestineradio.com/intel/station.php?id=192&stn=674 Voice of Justice], clandestineradio.com. Retrieved on 15 August 2014.</ref>
== See also == * [[Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting]], the Iranian publicly funded broadcaster.
