{{Infobox film | name = Imperfect Journey | image = | image_size = | caption = | director = Haile Gerima | producer = | writer = | narrator = | starring = See below | music = | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = 1994 | runtime = | country = [[Ethiopia]], [[Italy]], [[United States]] | language = [[Amharic language|Amharic]], [[English language|English]] | budget = | gross = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Imperfect Journey''''' is a 1994 [[Ethiopia]]n [[documentary film]] directed by [[Haile Gerima]].
== Plot summary == ''Imperfect Journey'' is a BBC commissioned film, exploring the political and psychic recovery of the Ethiopian people after the atrocities and political repression or "[[Red Terror (Ethiopia)|red terror]]" of the military junta of [[Mengistu Haile Mariam]].
Haile Gerima travelled to Ethiopia together with [[Ryszard Kapuściński]]. In the course of the journey they meet and talk with people from all levels of Ethiopian society.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Notes by Michael Dembrow|title=IMPERFECT JOURNEY-directed by Haile Gerima with Richard Kapuscinski|url=http://www.zehabesha.com/imperfect-journey-directed-by-haile-gerima-with-richard-kapuscinski/|website=Zehabesha|accessdate=1 October 2015|date=24 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Imperfect Journey|url=http://africa-archive.com/et/657|website=African Film Database|accessdate=1 October 2015}}</ref> The filmmaker questions the direction of the succeeding government and the will of the people in creating institutions guaranteeing their liberation.
Haile Gerima gave his thoughts on the film<ref>{{cite book|last1=Pfaff|first1=ed. by Françoise|title=Focus on African films|date=2004|publisher=Ind.|location=Bloomington|isbn=978-0253216687|pages=209|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=kjqh7O99pv0C&pg=PA209&lpg=PA209&dq=imperfect+journey+film&source=bl&ots=v9PesCrg4w&sig=a-extuDQFQgeqsT9OhJ3LdjMK6M&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwigvru3i-DPAhVBdz4KHcmYALc4ChDoAQgbMAA#v=onepage&q=imperfect%20journey%20film&f=false|accessdate=16 October 2016}}</ref> {{Quote|text=The title meant something incomplete. I made a film that was incomplete. Due to the political and cultural climate in which it was done, I made an "imperfect film". The journey was an imperfect journey, and the film is really about how young people's future is determined by a dysfunctional, underdeveloped African reality-a global reality but as it manifests itself in one country. |author=Françoise Pfaff |source=Focus on African Films (2004)}}
