{{Infobox hospital | Name = Nyangabgwe Hospital | Org/Group = [http://www.moh.gov.bw/ Botswana Ministry of Health] | Image = | image alt = | image_size = | Caption = | map_type = Botswana | map_size = <!-- width of the map in pixels (do not include "px"); default is 225 --> | map_alt = <!-- alternative text for map image, see WP:ALT for details --> | map_caption = Location in Botswana | Logo = <!-- Please conform to copyright --> | Logo Size = <!-- Use to limit the logo size --> | Region = [[Francistown]] | State = {| class="wikitable" |North East District |} | Country = [[Botswana]] | Coordinates = {{Coord|21|10|25|S| 27|30|45|E|}} | Address = <!-- Address of main building --> | HealthCare = <!-- UK:NHS. AU/CA: Medicare. ELSE freetext, e.g. Private --> | Funding = Government (Public) | Type = District | Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality (i.e. not a broad spectrum of specialities) and Type=Specialist/Teaching --> | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Emergency = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/IL/US: I/II/III/IV/V for Trauma certification level --> 24 Hours | Helipad = No | Affiliation = None | Patron = None | Network = <!-- Hospital network, non-owner --> | Beds = 550 beds<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electives.net/hospital/3480/preview|title=The Electives Network|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=11 October 2017}}</ref> | Founded = 1989 | Closed = <!-- Use if defunct, please also add to Category:Defunct hospitals --> | Website = None | Wiki-Links = <!-- Creates ""See also" field -->[[List of hospitals in Botswana]] }}
'''Nyangabgwe Referral Hospital''' is a health care institution located in [[Francistown]], [[Botswana]], The hospital was established in 1989.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gov.bw/en/Ministries--Authorities/Ministries/MinistryofHealth-MOH/Departments-of-MOH/MOA-Departments1/|title=Nyangabgwe Referral Hospital|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=11 October 2017}}</ref>
== History == Nyangabgwe Referral Hospital was established in 1989.It is a [[Government of Botswana]] health institution.The hospital is located in the second largest city of Botswana called Francistown. Nyangabgwe has 550 beds, (120-150) beds at the [[Internal medicine|Internal Med Department]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electives.net/hospital/3480/preview|title=Three major Referral hopitals in Botswana|last=|first=|date=|website=Electives.net|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=11 October 2017}}</ref> It is connected to the [[government of Botswana]] database system.
=== Internal Med Department === This department serves several wards at the hospital from the Male medical ward, Female medical ward, private ward and Isolation ward.
==Services== The hospital's 24-hour [[emergency department]] is able to cater for adults and children.The hospital departments include a Rehabilitation Centre, [[Pharmacy]], Anti-Retroviral (ARV) treatment for HIV/AIDS, Post Trauma Counseling Services, Occupational Services, [[Laundry]] Services, [[Kitchen]] Services and [[Mortuary]].
== Facilities == Princess Marina hospital has an annex, consisting of about 550 beds<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.electives.net/hospital/3480/preview|title=The Electives Network|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=18 October 2017}}</ref> space with the basic medical equipment for conducting series of diagnostic test.
