{{Infobox |name = Infobox/doc |bodystyle = |title = |titlestyle = |image = [[File:PANACREAS project logo.png|200 px|alt=PANACREAS project logo]] |imagestyle = |caption = Integrating chemical approaches to treat [[pancreatic cancer]]: making new leads for a cure |captionstyle = |headerstyle = background:#ccf; |labelstyle = background:#ddf; |datastyle = |header12 = Funding |label13 = |data13 = [[European Commission]] [[Seventh Framework Programme]] |header14 = Project |label15 = |data15 = Collaborative project |header16 = Grant agreement N° |label17 = |data17 = 256986 |header18 = Starting date |label19 = |data19 =March1st, 2011 |header20 = Duration |label21 = |data21 =5 years |header22= Website |label23 = |data23 = http://www.panacreas.eu<ref>http://www.panacreas.eu</ref> |header24 = Participants |label25 = UKB |data25 = [[University Hospital Bonn|Universitaetsklinikum Bonn]] <ref>http://www.uniklinik-bonn.de</ref> (coordinator) (GERMANY) |label26 = UNIGE |data26 = [[University of Genoa|Università degli Studi di Genova]] <ref>http://www.unige.it</ref>(ITALY) |label27 = CSIC |data27 = [[Spanish National Research Council|Agencia Estatal Consejo Superior de Investigaciones Cientificas]]<ref>http://www.csic.es</ref> (SPAIN) |label28 = EPFL |data28 = [[École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne]]<ref>http://www.epfl.ch/</ref> (SWITZERLAND) |label29 = CHUV |data29 = [[University Hospital of Lausanne]]<ref>http://www.chuv.ch/</ref> (SWITZERLAND) |label30 = USE |data30 =[[University of Seville|Universidad de Sevilla]]<ref>http://www.us.es /</ref> (SPAIN) |label31 = UNITN |data31= [[University of Trento|Università degli Studi di Trento]]<ref>http://www.unitn.it/</ref> (ITALY) |label32 = SIB |data32= [[Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics]]<ref>http://www.isb-sib.ch</ref> (SWITZERLAND) |label33 = ULUND |data33 = [[Lund University|Lunds Universitet]]<ref>http://www.lu.se/</ref> (SWEDEN) |label34 = DEBIO |data34= [[Debiopharm|Debiopharm SA]]<ref>http://www.debiopharm.com</ref> (SWITZERLAND) |label35 = Apointech |data35= Apointech S.L.<ref>http://www.apointech.com/</ref> (SPAIN) |label36 = ALTA |data36 = ALTA S.r.l.u.<ref>http://www.altaweb.eu</ref> (ITALY) }}
'''PANACREAS''' stands for “Integrating chemical approaches to treat [[pancreatic cancer]]: making new leads for a cure” and is being supported through Coordination Theme 1 (Health) of the [[European Community]]’s [[Seventh Framework Programme|FP7]].
== Summary ==
[[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|Pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma]] ([[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]]) is one of the most lethal human malignancies and a major health problem. It has been estimated that [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]] causes 34000 deaths per year in the [[European Union|EU]] alone.<ref>Ferlay J, et al. Ann Oncol 2007;18:581</ref> Despite considerable research efforts in the past decades, conventional treatment approaches, including [[surgery]], [[radiation therapy|radiation]], [[chemotherapy]], and combinations of these, have close to no impact on the course of this aggressive [[neoplasm]]. Therefore, virtually all of the patients diagnosed with [[pancreatic cancer|PC]] develop [[metastasis|metastases]] and die<ref>Li D, et al. Lancet 2004; 363:1049</ref> Given this scenario, the search for new [[drug]]s to combat [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]] progression and thus increase patient [[life expectancy]] and quality of life has been given high priority.<ref>Philip PA et al. Consensus Report of the National Cancer Institute Clinical Trials Planning Meeting on Pancreas Cancer Treatment. J Clin Oncol. 2009 Nov 20;27:5660-5669</ref> In particular, the [[National Cancer Institute]]’s Gastrointestinal Cancer Steering Committee has recently place major emphasis on the enhancement of "research to identify and validate the relevant targets and molecular pathways in [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]], [[cancer stem cell]]s, and the [[Microenvironment (biology)|microenvironment]]";
== Expected results ==
The work proposed in this program meets the need to reverse-translate the clinical issues encountered in [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]] into tailored researches to overcome such problems. Particularly, resistance to conventional therapeutics and high propensity to metastasize were taken into account when choosing for this project therapeutics that act through novel modes of action, and molecular targets that are emerging as crucially involved in [[metastasis]]. Our consortium will produce numerous new molecules to be tested and validated for their anticancer activity. This represents the conditio sine qua non for the finding of drugs that can be effective against [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]]. The most promising compounds will be evaluated in clinically relevant mouse models of [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]]. Finally strong [[proof of concept|proof-of-concept]] activity of any of these compounds will be a green light for proceeding to an [[Investigational New Drug]]-(IND)-enabling study. In the time frame of this project, we will aim to release one or more molecules that are ready to be tested in [[clinical studies]]. The ultimate goal of these efforts will be to arrest [[pancreatic ductal carcinoma|PDAC]] progression and reduce [[mortality rate|mortality]].
