{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Kindu |latin = Dioecesis Kinduensis |country = {{flag|Democratic Republic of the Congo}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bukavu|Bukavu]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 82,883 |population = 437,620 |population_as_of = 2003 |catholics = 171,070 |catholics_percent= 39.1 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Willy Ngumbi]], [[M. Afr.]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Kindu''' ({{lang-la|Kinduen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the cities of [[Kindu]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bukavu|Bukavu]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * April 23, 1956: Established as Apostolic Vicariate of Kindu from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Kongolo]] and the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Stanley-ville]] * November 10, 1959: Promoted as Diocese of Kindu
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Kindu ([[Latin Rite]]) ** Bishop Willy Ngumbi, M. Afr. (since 2007.04.25) ** Bishop [[Paul Mambe Mukanga]] (1979.03.15 – 2004.01.26) ** Bishop [[Albert Onyembo Lomandjo]], [[C.S.Sp.]] (1966.05.17 – 1978.01.17) ** Bishop [[Jean Fryns]], C.S.Sp. (1959.11.10 – 1965.07.02) * Vicars Apostolic of Kindu (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Jean Fryns, C.S.Sp. (1957.04.12 – 1959.11.10)
